benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/catalog/simplePlan - Add a simple plan entry in the current version of the catalog

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC12, @TC13, @TC19, @TC20, @TC21, @TC23, @TC24 cover successful creation with valid data.
Invalid Payload: @TC04, @TC05, @TC09, @TC18 cover malformed or invalid data inputs.
Duplicate Submission: @TC06 covers conflict when planId exists.
Missing Headers: @TC03 covers missing required header X-Killbill-CreatedBy.
Missing Request Body: @TC08 covers empty request body.
Malformed JSON: @TC09 covers invalid JSON input.
Service Unavailability: @TC11, @TC24 cover catalog or dependent services being down or degraded.
Maximum/Minimum Values: @TC12, @TC13 cover boundary testing for field lengths and values.
Unsupported Methods: @TC14 covers method not allowed scenario.
Large Payloads: @TC15 covers very large request data.
Security: @TC18 covers injection and XSS testing.
Add when catalog is empty or partially populated: @TC19, @TC20.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets requiring pagination.
Authorization: No explicit tests for invalid or expired tokens or user permissions beyond missing header.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate multiple rapid requests to verify throttling.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios testing cache headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Timeouts: No tests for network or server timeout scenarios.
Recovery from network failures: Limited to @TC16, but lacks detailed retries or idempotency checks.
Backward compatibility: Only partially covered in @TC21, more detailed version-specific tests could be added.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination handling for large datasets.
Include explicit authorization tests with invalid or expired credentials.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to verify system resilience.
Add scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation.
Include timeout and network failure recovery tests with retries.
Expand backward compatibility testing with different API versions.
Test for idempotency and repeated submissions to prevent duplicate entries.
